com.ace.lewissketch
Class MoleculeToMol

java.lang.Object
  com.ace.lewissketch.MoleculeToMol
All Implemented Interfaces:
LewisConstants
 class MoleculeToMol
extends Object
implements LewisConstants

Converts a given Molecule object to an equivalent MOL string. Companion to class LsMolToData. MOL FILE SPECIFICATIONS found at: http://www.mdl.com/downloads/public/ctfile/ctfile.pdf

getHeaderBlock

private String getHeaderBlock(int numAtoms,
                              int numBonds)
Header Block: note on field types: i3 means integer length 3, c5 means char length 5 line 1: molecule name (unformatted, max 80 chars), or blank line 2: c2 - user's first and last initials c8 - program name c10 - date/time: MMDDYYHHmmdd c2 - dimensional codes i2 - scaling factor 1 f10.5 - scaling factor 2 (ex:0000.00000) f12.5 - Energy i16 - Internal Registry # if MDL form line 3: a comment line or blank line 4: Counts Line: i3 - # atoms (max 255) i3 - # bonds (max 255) i3 - # atom lists (max 30) [lll] c3 - obsolete (blank) [fff] i3 - chiral flag (" 0"=not chiral, " 1"=chiral) [ccc] i3 - # stext entries (MDL ISIS/Desktop use only) [sss] c12- obsolete (blank) [xxxrrrpppiii] i3 - # lines of additional properties including M END (obsolete) c6 - Ctab version (EX: " V2000")

Parameters:
numAtoms - the number of atoms in the molecule
numBonds - the number of bonds in the molecule
Returns:
the header block

getAliasBlock

private String getAliasBlock(List<Atom> atomList)
Aliases for all C atoms are added so that JPEGs created by Marvin from MOL files will display all C atoms (instead of just angles). This route is not necessary if the figure will be displayed in MarvinView, where we can use a parameter to set the C atoms to show their labels.

Parameters:
atomList - the list of atoms in the molecule
Returns:
the alias block of the MOL representation

getDateString

private String getDateString()
Return a string representing the current date and time in Mol file format which is MMDDYYHHmmss Notes: Calendar.MONTH seems to work 0..11, so add 1 to get 1..12 Calendar.YEAR is 4-digit (ex: 2005) but Mol Files use 2-digit (ex: 05), and so are NOT "Y2K Compatible"!!

Returns:
a string representing the current date and time in MOL format

getAtomBlock

private String getAtomBlock(List<Atom> atomList)
Gets a string representing the atom block. For each atom line: 
 xxxxx.xxxxyyyyy.yyyyzzzzz.zzzz aaaddcccssshhhbbbvvv[remainder unused]
 x/y/z coordinates: xxxxx.xxxxyyyyy.yyyyzzzzz.zzzz
 one single blank
 aaa - atom symbol, left justified
 dd  - mass difference (obsolete,use M ISO property below)
 ccc - charge (M CHG will supercede; tradition says set it anyway ;)
 sss - atom stereo parity (ignored just use "  0")
 hhh - hydrogen count + 1 (we'll use 0, meaning all H atoms are drawn)
 bbb - stereo care box (we don't care, so 0)
 vvv - valence (0 means no marking)
remainder of fields not needed or used, so can end line here

Parameters:
atomList - the list of atoms
Returns:
the MOL format atom block

getBondBlock

private String getBondBlock(List<Atom> atomList,
                            List<Bond> bondList)
Gets a string representing the atom block. For each bond: 
 format: 111222tttsssxxxrrrcc
 111 - atom # (as listed in atom block, first atom is #1)
 222 - atom # of second atom
 ttt - bond type (1=single, 2=triple, 3=double, we dont use others)
 sss - bond stereo (we dont use, so 0)
 xxx - not used (blank)
 ccc - reacting center status code (we dont use, so 0)

Parameters:
atomList - the list of atoms
bondList - the list of bonds
Returns:
the MOL format bond block

getAtomPropertyBlock

private String getAtomPropertyBlock(String propTag,
                                    List<Atom> atomList)
Gets an atom property block containing 0 or more property lines in the format: 
 "M PPP NN INN VVV ..."
where PPP is the property tag, NN is the number of items on this line (max 8) INN is the atom number, and VVV is the property value.

Parameters:
propTag - the tag for the property
atomList - the list of atoms
Returns:
the MOL format atom property block

getBondPropertyBlock

private String getBondPropertyBlock(String propTag,
                                    List<Bond> bondList)
Gets a bond property block containing 0 or more property lines in the format: 
 "M PPP NN INN VVV ..."
where PPP is the property tag, NN is the number of items on this line (max 8) INN is the bond number, and VVV is the property value. Currently the only bond property in use is "CLB" (bond color), but this method is written to easily add others.

Parameters:
propTag - the tag for the property
bondList - the list of bonds
Returns:
the MOL format bond property block

chargeToMolCode

private int chargeToMolCode(int charge)
Gets a charge value for ATOM BLOCK (taken from CTFILE document, chapter 2). This value is deprecated and ignored if M__CHG lines are added, but it is "tradition" to use these codes on an Atom line anyway.

Parameters:
charge - the charge
Returns:
the charge code for the atom block
